Ja hvis hun vilde love aldrig at gj&#xF8;re det
ved ham eller nogen anden vilde h. kurere
hende, ellers skulde hu blive det hu var.
S. maatte hu til at love og h. kurerede hende.</danish_manuscript>
  <english_manuscript>The witches churned on Saint Hans eve. One night a girl went and smeared Jens Ilder's door with it, because she wanted to bewitch his cattle. But he scraped it off in one place and then he loaded his rifle and shot into it and then he hit the girl and shot her back full of it. Then she had to come to him for a remedy. Well, if she promised to never do that to him or anybody else again, he'd cure her, otherwise she could just stay as she was. Then she had to promise that and then he cured her.</english_manuscript>
  <danish_publication>Heksene de kj&#xE6;rnede st. Hans aften. En aften gik en pige og smurte Jens Ilders d&#xF6;re med det sm&#xF6;r, for hun vilde vel sagt forhekse hans kreaturer. Men han skrabte det sammen p&#xE5; &#xE9;t sted, og s&#xE5; ladede han hans b&#xF8;sse og skod i det, og s&#xE5; ramte han pigen og sk&#xF8;d hendes ryg fuld af det. S&#xE5; m&#xE5;tte hun til ham om at f&#xE5; r&#xE5;d for det. Ja, hvis hun vilde love aldrig mere at gj&#xF8;re det ved ham eller nogen anden, vilde han kurere hende, ellers skulde hun blive det, hun var. Det m&#xE5;tte hun til at love, og s&#xE5; kurerede han hende.</danish_publication>
  <english_publication>The witches they churned on Saint Hans eve. One night a girl went and smeared Jens Ilder&#x2019;s door with that butter because she wanted to bewitch his cattle. But he scraped it off in one place and then he loaded his rifle and shot into it and then he hit the girl and shot her back full of it. Then she had to come to him for a remedy. Well, if she promised to never do that to him or anybody else again, he&#x2019;d cure her, otherwise she could just stay as she was. Then she had to promise that and then he cured her.</english_publication>
